comments: Walker (BOS) fumbles the ball as he gathers, but he is able to recover the ball and maintain his newly established pivot foot prior to passing.
Walker (BOS) is able to save the ball and pass it before stepping into the backcourt.
Turner (IND) legally contests Brown's (BOS) jump shot attempt.

During the rebound, Sabonis (IND) and Pritchard (BOS) try to retrieve the loose ball and any contact as they both reach for it is deemed incidental. After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of Pacers possession stands.

Thompson (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact initiated by Sabonis (IND) during his drive to the basket. Any contact to Sabonis' arm during the drive is deemed marginal as it does not affect his ability to cleanly gather the ball.
Brown (BOS) steps out of bounds upon receiving the pass and prior to starting his dribble.
Sabonis (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Walker's (BOS) path and absorbs the contact.
During the rebound, Sabonis (IND) and Williams III (BOS) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Turner (IND) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact as he moves alongside Walker (BOS) during his drive.

Walker (BOS) engages on the legal pick by Sabonis (IND) as he briefly grasps and immediately releases Sabonis' jersey while disengaging. The contact does not affect Sabonis' ability to maintain his legal screening position.
Walker (BOS) legally contests Sabonis' (IND) jump shot attempt and the ball remains in play when it bounces off of the top of the backboard.
Sabonis (IND) moves laterally into Walker's (BOS) path in the backcourt and the contact affects his SQBR.
During the inbound, Brogdon (IND) and Walker (BOS) mutually engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.

Holiday (IND) places a resting hand on Pritchard's (BOS) arm and the contact is marginal as it does not affect his ability to make his intended pass. Pritchard jumps and releases his pass prior to returning to the ground.
Sumner (IND) and Tatum (BOS) make incidental leg contact off ball.
Brogdon (IND) makes contact to Walker's (BOS) arm that affects his SQBR.  The foul occurs before any possible 8 second violation.
Walker (BOS) and McDermott (IND) mutually engage and quickly disengage as marginal contact occurs on the defensive switch.
Tatum (BOS) returns to the ground after the rebound and makes incidental foot to foot contact with Sabonis (IND) that causes him to lose his balance.
Holiday (IND) commits a take foul on Williams III (BOS).
